OL,3,CLabour to drop #28 billion-a-year
OL,4,Cgreen spending pledge
OL,6,FLast year, Labour changed its original
OL,7,Fpolicy by saying the #28 billion-a-
OL,8,Fyear spending target would likely be
OL,9,Fmet in the second half of a first
OL,10,Fparliament, rather than immediately,
OL,11,Fif the party wins the next election.
OL,13,FThe party has since insisted the
OL,14,Fpledge is subject to its fiscal rules,
OL,15,Fwhich include getting debt falling as
OL,16,Fa percentage of GDP, as it seeks to
OL,17,Freassure voters it would handle the
OL,18,Feconomy responsibly in government.
