OL,6,F"On the day that Labour are finalising
OL,7,Ftheir manifesto, Keir Starmer is
OL,8,Ftorpedoing what he has claimed to be
OL,9,Fhis central economic policy purely for
OL,10,Fshort-term campaigning reasons.
OL,12,F"He must explain how he can keep the
OL,13,F#28 billion spending when he is
OL,14,Ffinally admitting he doesn't have a
OL,15,Fplan to pay for it.
OL,17,F"This black hole will inevitably mean
OL,18,Fthousands of pounds in higher taxes
OL,19,Ffor working people. That's why Labour
OL,20,Fwill take Britain back to square one."
